The technical advisory committee consists of the following members, appointed by the Secretary:
A board certified anesthesiologist licensed and practicing in the State, nominated by the Maryland Society of Anesthesiologists;
A certified addiction medicine specialist licensed and practicing in the State, nominated by the Maryland Society for Addiction Medicine;
A pharmacist licensed and practicing in the State;
A medical professional, licensed and practicing in the State, who is treating cancer patients; and
A board certified physician specializing in the treatment of patients with pain, licensed and practicing in the State, nominated by the Maryland Society of Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation.
